<h1>Problem 2298 - DGGMaths Riddles Week 10, P2 of 4, NC</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>Suppose \(N\) is the product of \(n\) distinct primes. Prove that there are at least \(7^n\) ordered triples \((x,y,z)\) of positive integers with \[\frac{1}{x} + \frac{1}{y} + \frac{1}{z} = \frac{1}{N}.\]</p>
